men scientists face, while highlighting research-based solutions to help overcome these obstacles. She presents groundbreaking studies in social psychology and organizational behavior that are informing novel approaches for combating historic and ongoing inequities.Through a combined focus on personal experiences and social-science research, this timely book provides both a path toward greater gender equity and an inspiring vision of science and scientists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aSex discrimination against womenzUnited States2DLC. 0aSex discrimination against womenzUnited States. 0aSex discrimination against women-United States. 0aSex discrimination in sciencezUnited States2DLC. 0aSex discrimination in sciencezUnited States. 0aSex discrimination in science-United States. 0aWomen in sciencezUnited States2DLC. 0aWomen in sciencezUnited States. 0aWomen in science-United States. 0aWomenxVocational guidancezUnited States2DLC. 0aWomenxVocational guidancezUnited States. 0aWomen-Vocational guidance-United States. 7aSCIENCE / Philosophy & Social Aspects.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023 Englishz978311131922308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2023z9783111318646oZDB-23-DPH40uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/muno2061440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231556347423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231556347/original  a978-3-11-074967-0  Columbia Univ